code:
```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('obesity.json')

# Plot histogram of BMI
sns.histplot(data=data, x='BMI', kde=True, color='blue')
plt.axvline(data['BMI'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean BMI: {:.2f}'.format(data['BMI'].mean()))
plt.legend()
plt.title('What is the distribution of BMI among the population?')
plt.xlabel('BMI')
plt.ylabel('Count')

# Show plot
plt.show()
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('obesity.json')

# Plot
sns.set(style="whitegrid")
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))
sns.barplot(x='Country', y='Obesity (%)', data=data, ax=ax, palette='Blues_d')
ax.set_xlabel('Country', fontsize=14)
ax.set_ylabel('Obesity (%)', fontsize=14)
ax.set_title('What is the distribution of obesity levels among different countries?', fontsize=16, wrap=True)
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.tight_layout()

# Return plot
plt.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.boxplot(x="Obesity Level", y="BMI", data=data, palette="Set3")
    plt.title("What is the relationship between BMI and obesity levels?", wrap=True)
    ax.set(xlabel='Obesity Level', ylabel='BMI')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
